                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">367.1164 R 54/172: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-03T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 3, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>566. Your 1084, October 29, 11 a.m. The Department approves your action in
                    drawing Robert College taxation question to Foreign Minister’s attention. It
                    would be particularly regretted if Turkish Government should change its policy
                    towards the College now, when Turkish officers are attending the school and when
                    United States War Department has manifested its desire to assist Turkey by
                    assigning four qualified United States Army Officers as instructors there, at a
                    time when their release from United States Army represented notable
                        sacrifice.<note n="62" xml:id="d953fn62">In telegram No. 585, March 27,
                        1943, 6 p.m., Ambassador Steinhardt reported: “As a result of personal
                        intervention of Prime Minister the very substantial minimum profits tax
                        assessed against Robert College has been set aside.”
                        (367.1164R54/180)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
